The owner/operator shall maintain the following records:  

a) The type an d amount of each solvent  used on a daily basis;  
b) The POC and formaldehyde emissions at the stack of S -8, the POC emissions 
from the slip steam withdrawn  from the exhaust of S -1, and the POC 
emissions from the use of ION solvents at S -8 on a monthly basis;  
c) Monthly emission calculations shall be totaled for each consecutive twelve-month period;  
d) Source test reports and emission rates derived from source test data.  

The owner/operator shall maintain all records for at least five years and shall make them available for District inspection upon request. (
